transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra, Quinn speaking, how can I help you?

Speaker 2: Yeah, I just, can I put a hold on my prescription for a couple of months?

Speaker 1: You absolutely can, let me pull up your prescription.

Speaker 2: Yeah, because I'm going in for surgery and I won't be able to take any pills for a while.

Speaker 1: Okay, no worries then.

Speaker 2: I can push you out five months and you can always shorten that if you need to.

Speaker 1: Okay, so let's do the five months and then if I need it sooner I'll call back.

Speaker 2: And you can also request more time if need be as well.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: Do you want to take my name and extension?

Speaker 1: Yes.

Speaker 2: So that way if you do need to change or alter anything, you know, you can reach me directly.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right, so my name is Quinn.

Speaker 1: Quinn.

Speaker 2: And my, excuse me, extension is 0035.

Speaker 1: Okay, thank you so much.

Speaker 2: You are very welcome, sir.

Speaker 1: Anything else that I could do for you?

Speaker 2: No, so it's automatically on hold now?

Speaker 1: Yes, sir.

Speaker 2: I just changed that for you.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All righty.

Speaker 1: All you, excuse me, you're all set.

Speaker 2: Thank you, I appreciate it.

Speaker 1: You have a great day.

Speaker 2: You too.

Speaker 1: Okay, bye.

Speaker 2: Bye.
